&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Consultant Gynaecologist with a special interest in Gynae Oncology&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Permanent - Full-time Position&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join an innovative team working across Staffordshire, Shropshire and East Cheshire. The post-holder will be required to provide the full range of general gynaecological skills within the multi-disciplinary team. There are 23 Consultants (including this post) that provide care within the Directorate of Obstetrics and Gynaecology.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This post is based at University Hospital of North Midlands. Clinical Duties will be across both the Royal Stoke and County Hospital Sites.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The University Hospital is the main teaching hospital for the Keele University Undergraduate Medical School and there are close ties with the University of Keele and Staffordshire University. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will have MRCOG or appropriate specialist qualification, ATSM training in Gynae Oncology. The candidate will preferably need to have Colposcopy Accreditation, have CCT or equivalent (‘equivalence’ must be confirmed by PMETB/GMC by date of interview) and be on the GMC Specialist Register or be eligible for entry within 6 months of date of interview.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing date: 23rd November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date: 14th December 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
